(Shutterstock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - The Polokwane municipality in Limpopo has appealed to residents to use water sparingly as Eskom's power cuts caused water shortages in some areas, a spokesperson said on Tuesday."Already some residential areas within the city and other areas are affected by water shortage," Tidimalo Chuene said in a statement.Reservoir levels were very low and high-lying areas were most affected."The municipality is working on sourcing more water tankers to provide temporary aid to affected areas. A water tanker will be moving between the affected areas," she said.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.